Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce.

In a #small bowl, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @Mozzarella Cheese{1/2%cup}, and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Set aside.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil.

Once water is boiling, add @Penne Pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a large, preferably ovenproof, #pan over medium-high heat.

Add @Beyond Burger{8%oz} patties crumbled and @Italian Seasoning{1%tbsp}; cook, breaking up patties into pieces, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high.

Stir @Marinara{1%14oz cup}, @Cream Sauce Base{4%oz}, @Cream Cheese{2%tbsp}, and @Butter{1%tbsp} into pan. Add @Chili Flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Bring to a simmer.

Stir in @Spinach{5%oz} (do so in batches, allowing spinach to wilt slightly before adding more). Cook, stirring, until spinach has wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.

Stir penne and 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water into pan. Taste and season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Evenly sprinkle pasta with panko mixture.

> For 4 servings, stir in 1/2 cup reserved pasta cooking water. If the pan feels too crowded, carefully pour everything into pot used for pasta; transfer mixture back to ovenproof pan before broiling or baking.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer pasta to a #baking dish{} before sprinkling with panko mixture.

Broil pasta on top rack until panko is golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide between plates and serve.